						<summary>

						<p>On the east wall of the Śankarālaya.</p>						

						<p>Vikrama, Vaiśākha.</p>						

						<p>This can be dated to 17th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>States that the <hi rend="italic">jayastaṁbha</hi> was installed by Sadaśivamakhin which enables the god names of Lord Śiva i.e., Hara, Hari and Sūrya.</p>						

